	  <title>The rank of a system of linear equations</title>
	
	  <showme>
		    <statement.showme>
			      <para>
            <para.body>Find the rank of the system of linear equations</para.body>
         </para>
			      <math.display>
				        <latex>
					
\begin{array}{rcrcrcr}
x &amp; + &amp; 3y &amp; &amp; &amp; = &amp; 4 \\
  &amp;   &amp;    &amp; &amp; z &amp; = &amp; -1
\end{array}
					
				</latex>
			      </math.display>
		    </statement.showme>
		    <answer.showme type="Solution">
         <answer.showme.block>
            <answer.showme.block.body>
			            <para>
                  <para.body>The coefficient matrix of this system of linear equations is</para.body>
               </para>
			            <math.display>
				              <latex>
					
\begin{array}{rrr|r}
{\color{red} 1} &amp; 3 &amp; 0 &amp; 4 \\
0 &amp; 0 &amp; {\color{red} 1} &amp; -1
\end{array}
					
				</latex>
			            </math.display>
			            <para>
                  <para.body>The non-augmented coefficient matrix has two leading 1’s. Therefore the rank of this system of linear equations is <math>
                        <latex>2</latex>
                     </math>.</para.body>
               </para>
		          </answer.showme.block.body>
         </answer.showme.block>
      </answer.showme>
	  </showme>
	
	
	
	  <showme>
		    <statement.showme>
			      <para>
            <para.body>Suppose a system of linear equations has a coefficient matrix which row reduces to </para.body>
         </para>
			      <math.display>
				        <latex>
					
\begin{array}{rrrrrr|r}
1 &amp; 3 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 7 &amp; 0 &amp; 1 \\
0 &amp; 0 &amp; 1 &amp; 0 &amp; 5 &amp; 0 &amp; -1 \\
0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 1 &amp; 1 &amp; 0 &amp; 4 \\
0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 1 &amp; 5
\end{array}
					
				</latex>
			      </math.display>
			      <para>
            <para.body>Find the rank of the system.</para.body>
         </para>
		    </statement.showme>
		    <answer.showme type="Solution">
         <answer.showme.block>
            <answer.showme.block.body>
			            <para>
                  <para.body>Indeed, the given matrix is already in RREF. Let us identify its leading 1’s:</para.body>
               </para>
			            <math.display>
				              <latex>
					
\begin{array}{rrrrrr|r}
{\color{red} 1} &amp; 3 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 7 &amp; 0 &amp; 1 \\
0 &amp; 0 &amp; {\color{red} 1} &amp; 0 &amp; 5 &amp; 0 &amp; -1 \\
0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; {\color{red} 1} &amp; 1 &amp; 0 &amp; 4 \\
0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; {\color{red} 1} &amp; 5
\end{array}
					
				</latex>
			            </math.display>
			            <para>
                  <para.body>So the non-augmented part of the row reduced coefficient matrix contains 4 leading 1’s. Therefore the rank of this system of linear equations is 4.</para.body>
               </para>
		          </answer.showme.block.body>
         </answer.showme.block>
      </answer.showme>
	  </showme>
